AWS Elastic Beanstalk:
An orchestration service for deploying web applications and services. It supports multiple languages (Java, .NET, PHP, Node.js, Python, Ruby, Go, and Docker) 
and handles capacity provisioning, load balancing, and auto-scaling. 

AWS App Runner: 
A fully managed container service that connects directly to your source code or container image to deploy scalable web apps and APIs. 
Note: AWS will stop accepting new customers for App Runner on April 30, 2026; users are encouraged to migrate to Amazon ECS Express Mode. 

AWS Amplify:
A purpose-built platform for frontend web and mobile developers to build and host full-stack applications with built-in authentication, storage, 
and CI/CD workflows. 

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Serverless & Container Services
AWS Lambda: 
A serverless compute service that runs code in response to events (FaaS). It automatically scales and bills only for the actual compute time used. 

Amazon Elastic Container Service (ECS): 
A highly scalable container management service that allows you to run, stop, and manage Docker containers on a cluster. 

AWS Fargate:
A serverless compute engine for containers that works with both ECS and Amazon EKS, removing the need to manage underlying servers. 

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Supporting Application Services
Amazon API Gateway: 
A fully managed service for creating, publishing, and securing REST, HTTP, and WebSocket APIs at any scale.

Amazon Simple Notification Service (SNS): 
A managed pub/sub messaging service for system-to-system and app-to-person notifications.

AWS App Studio: 
A generative AI-powered service that uses natural language to build secure, enterprise-grade business applications in minutes.

Amazon Lightsail: 
Provides easy-to-use virtual private servers (VPS), storage, and networking for simple web applications and websites.
